curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/6926' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM8969-1/SGM8969-2", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM8969-1/2 are a family of single and dual  rail-to-rail input and output operational amplifiers, which  are optimized for low voltage, low noise and high  precision operation. These devices can operate from  1.8V to 5.5V single supply, while consuming only  1.1mA quiescent current per amplifier at 5.5V.  The SGM8969-1/2 feature a 240μV maximum input  offset. They exhibit a high gain-bandwidth product of  50MHz and a slew rate of 20V/μs. These specifications  make the operational amplifiers appropriate for various  applications.  The SGM8969-1 is available in a Green SOT-23-5  package. The SGM8969-2 is available in Green SOIC-8  and TDFN-3×3-8L packages. They are specified over  the extended industrial temperature range (-40℃ to  +125℃).    "}'
